Biden prizes stability and a boycott would be a destabilizing and provocative act;
Biden was confronted with a somewhat similar situation in Saudi Arabia with MBS and the Kashoggi murder and chose a moderate approach;
It's early in his term and he has had little opportunity to work directly with Xi as President;
A dramatic move like a boycott would invite economic consequences of some kind, which amid a recovery as a new President in a sharply divided nation, Biden would be unlikely to invite;
When the US Olympic committee may have the authority to make a decision, that's not the group one would turn to if you're looking for moral exemplars. The corporate sponsors have a lot invested in the games, even if it's just the winter games, and it's difficult to imagine a world where the Olympic committee takes a moral stand. Thoughts?
